if ! ./alfred-pinboard-rs config --authorization $1; then echo "Couldn't set user credentials!!!" else echo "Successfully set user credentials." fi
output=$(./alfred-pinboard-rs config --fuzzy $1) if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then echo $output else echo "Fuzzy set to: $1" fi

cat << EOB
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<items> <item uid="1" arg="true" valid="YES" autocomplete="Yes"> <title>Enable Fuzzy Search</title> <icon>fuzzy.png</icon> </item>
<item uid="2" arg="false" valid="YES" autocomplete="No"> <title>Disable Fuzzy Search</title> <icon>unfuzzy.png</icon> </item> </items>
EOB
output=$(./alfred-pinboard-rs config --tag-numbers $1) if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then echo $output else echo "No. items to show: $1" fi
Set max. no. of tags to show.
output=$(./alfred-pinboard-rs config --bookmark-numbers $1) if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then echo $output else echo "No. items to show: $1" fi
Set max. no. of bookmarks to show
output=$(./alfred-pinboard-rs config --suggest-tags $1) if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then echo $output else echo "Tag suggestion: $1" fi

cat << EOB
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<items> <item uid="" arg="true" valid="YES" autocomplete="Yes"> <title>Enable Popular Tags</title> <icon>suggest.png</icon> </item>
<item uid="" arg="false" valid="YES" autocomplete="No"> <title>Disable Popular Tags</title> <icon>no_suggest.png</icon> </item> </items>
EOB
output=$(./alfred-pinboard-rs config --shared $1) if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then echo $output else echo "Sharing Bookmarks: $1" fi

cat << EOB
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<items> <item uid="" arg="true" valid="YES"> <title>Enable Shared Bookmarking</title> <icon>unlocked.png</icon> </item>
<item uid="" arg="false" valid="YES"> <title>Enable Private Bookmarking</title> <icon>locked.png</icon> </item> </items>
EOB

<?xml version="1.0"?>
<items> <item uid="tagonly" arg="true" valid="YES" autocomplete="Yes"> <title>Search ONLY tag field</title> <icon>tagonly.png</icon> </item>
<item uid="des" arg="false" valid="YES" autocomplete="No"> <title>Search ALL fields (tags/titles/notes)</title> <icon>bookmarks.png</icon> </item> </items>
EOB
output=$(./alfred-pinboard-rs config --tags-only $1) if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then echo $output else echo "Tag ONLY: $1" fi

output=$(./alfred-pinboard-rs config --auto-update $1) if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then echo $output else echo "Auto-update of cache: $1" fi
output=$(./alfred-pinboard-rs config --toread $1) if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then echo $output else echo "New bookmarks will be to-read: $1" fi

cat << EOB
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<items> <item uid="tagonly" arg="true" valid="YES" autocomplete="Yes"> <title>Set new bookmars as TOREAD</title> <icon>toread.png</icon> </item>
<item uid="des" arg="false" valid="YES" autocomplete="No"> <title>Do NOT set new bookmars as TOREAD</title> <icon>toread.png</icon> </item> </items>
EOB

This is a Workflow to manage your Pinboard bookmarks. I mainly wrote this so I can learn/practice Rust language. Make sure you set your authenticaton token first before first use. Detailed instructions are available at https://github.com/spamwax/alfred-pinboard-rs
